<br>
Technology is an amazing thing, in 1890 it was predicted that we would exceed the productivity of the worlds food suppliers within 12 years, an lo!  Technology did expand our supplies to permit continued growth.  Then again in 1930, 1957 and 1998 were the same prophesies of doom and gloom made.  Despite our 'Quiverful' parents and their families of 12 to 19, we continue to find new and better ways to feed our population.  Should this fail, economics will take over.  Water is everywhere.  Were it to become a population control, people would start selling it (more than just these evian guys) - same goes for food.  Where limits arise money is made in overcoming them.<br>
<br>
Not to offend, for you have a beautifully romanitc view of our earth as a mother of us all, or possibly us as paracites on her, but I see no evidence of her as a consiousness.  I do think however that worshipping her would be far better than the great <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>WAR SANTA</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> we have now.  We can be responsible citizens of the planet without making her into something more than she is.  Just as a deist can make beautiful asertions about the existance of god, when it becomes a theist it just aint so.<br>
