I don't believe that I'll see my grandfather again, or several friends, or anyone else that is dead, either. Of course we miss them--it's natural. It's human. <br>
Is it much nicer, much more comforting to hold the belief that one will be reunited with their loved ones after death? I'm sure it is. But I can't believe in or find comfort in something that I simply know is implausible. I find other sources of comfort. Memories, pictures, seeing traits of my grandfather in myself (like my love for lettuce drenched in sour cream &amp; salt) or my family...things like that. <br>
